es methods from history, gender studies, and military science to reveal the extent to which the Great War challenged these men’s senses of masculinity, and to which the resulting dynamics influenced their attitudes and loyalties.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aAllegiancezCzech RepubliczBohemiaxHistory. 0aMasculinityzCzech RepubliczBohemiaxHistory. 0aMilitary moralezCzech RepubliczBohemiaxHistory. 0aSoldierszCzech RepubliczBohemiaxAttitudes. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xParticipation, CzechxHistoriography. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xParticipation, Czech. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War I.2bisacsh  aanalysis.  aauthority.  acombat.  acontemporary history.  aczech.  adebate.  aeurope.  aeuropean history.  aexperience.  aforgotten history.  agender studies.  agreat war.  ahard times.  ahistorical literature.  ahistorical.  ahistory buff.  aidentity.  ajournals.  alife story.  aloyalty.  amasculinity.  amilitary science.  amilitary.  amodern history.  aovercoming obstacles.  apostwar.  aprivate writings.  arealistic.  asex.  asoldiers.  atrue story.  awartime.  aworld history.  aworld war.  awwi.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311099772940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781789205428?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781789205428423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781789205428/original  a978-3-11-099772-9  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK